inn1.comm: nice flick to fine leg to get off the mark, moved right across his stumps
that's a very circumspect start by Barath, late movement after pitching, the batsman was poking at it, feet all over the place
nudges it off the pads and Vinay's optimistic again with the appeal, that wasn't hitting
gets beside the line and knocks it to the off side
nice shape away from the right-hander, Simmons gives him respect and leaves it alone
gets right across his stumps to cover the line to defend, decent start by Vinay
and another false shot by Barath, he chased at a short and wide one which climbed after pitching, half hearted appeal
he fires that a mile wide outside the off stump, no way he was hitting that
better delivery, closer to the off stump and left alone, he shoulders arms
he tempts him again with a short delivery shaping away outside the off stump, Barath had half a mind to chase that
pitches it up this time and gets him to defend on the front foot
lands it on middle and leg, he shuffles and clips it off his pads

the bowler deserves all the credit for that one, Barath was circumspect from the very beginning with the away swinging delivery, Yadav tempted him into poking at another delivery which was pitched up outside off, he followed the movement, his feet were all over the place, edged and no doubts about that
edged and just short of second slip! Played it with soft hands
straight this time and he gets behind the line and defends solidly
hurries him up a bit with pace, he gets beside the line and knocks it softly to the off side
hops at the crease and chops it to the off side, Vinay's running in hard
keeps it straight and forces him to play, he defends back to the bowler but didn't appear in full control of the shot
now he pitches it up and the batsman is happy to let that go
just lets go of the bat handle as he tucks it to the on side
that was close to being called a wide outside off, jagged away after pitching and he lashed at it
86 mph, lands it a touch wide outside off and he shoulders arms
139 kph, pitches it up and swings away, he went forward to drive but turned the face of the bat, the ball rolled towards point
140 kph, lands it a touch outside the off stump and the batsman lets it go to the keeper

confident appeal for a lbw but the umpire Ravi shakes his head, landed just outside off and came back in, appeared to hit him in line with leg stump as he defended forward, looked out to me on the replay
opens the face and angles it down to third man
risky! He drove at it wide outside the off stump, thick outside edge and just wide of the diving second slip (Rohit), raced to third man
gets across and defends back to the bowler
gets across and defends to the off side
that's a classic shot, full and swinging away from the right-hander, he gets beside the line and drives it past the gap between point and cover
87 mph, pitched up outside off and the batsman lets it go

Dropped Rohit should have taken that, Yadav gets it to swing away and the ball flies off the face of the bat almost as he shapes to drive, Rohit went to his right and got behind the ball but fluffed the catch, Rohit in all his frustration flung the ball away and they took an extra run
and another fizzer of a delivery, close to the edge again, this was a touch shorter
chips down the track to thud it down the ground but he found mid-off
shades of Greenidge there, gets across his stumps, gets on one leg and whips it away behind square on the on side
full and driven but straight to cover
confident appeal for an lbw but he got an inside edge, he was stuck to the crease
just a hint slower and he dabbed it softly down towards point and set off for a quick single
gets another inside edge, looking a little circumspect against Vinay
that's a 1000 runs in ODIs for Simmons, gets down the pitch and drives firmly past the covers, good fielding to cut it down to two
he ends the over in a flourish, not a bad delivery actually, not much width but he improvised well by slicing it and timing it well, beats backward point and third man

Excellent take by Raina at third slip! Samuels isn't sure so he's waiting for the third umpire to take a look, Samuels was squared up at the crease, tried to work it to the on side, got a leading edge and Raina had to dive low to his right at third slip, he just about managed to get his hands under the ball, needed a few replays to confirm that
stays on the backfoot and defends to the off side
and Simmons had a close call there, lands it on the corridor outside off and he had to play at it, close to shaving the outside edge
turns the face of the bat and tries to work it away to the on side
keeps it on that line outside off and he shoulders arms
fullish and swinging away outside the off stump, softly pats it to the off side
comes round the wicket and he gets him to defend on the backfoot
full delivery aiming for the yorker, he drills it to the off side
that's all elegance! Angles it on the pads and all he has to do is whip it away wide of square leg, nicely timed
comes over the wicket this time and he sprays it wide outside off, no shot offered
in the length to drive on the front foot but he ends up pushing it straight to mid-off
nice line and length on the off stump, gets him to defend to the off side
angles it away from the right-hander and he pushes it to the off side
chips down the track and thumps it down the pitch, Yadav gets a hand to it and nearly deflects it to the stumps, had Bravo on all-fours there as he scampered back
sprays it down the leg side
Simmons hops at the crease, the ball clips his pads and rolls away, Yadav's really hurrying him up for pace here
that's a good response! Simmons was expecting another pacy short one, stays back, fetches it from the off stump and pulls over midwicket
poor delivery, full toss swinging away outside off, that was asking to be spanked, punches it wide of backward point
pushes it down the pitch
shuffles and nudges it down to fine leg
shuffles a bit and he nudges it off his pads, the ball rolls to the on side
good running, dropped it with soft hands to the off side and set off quickly
loses control of the inswinger and sprays it down the leg side
half-hearted appeal, gets his front foot outside the line of the off stump, the ball strikes him on the pad, that wasn't hitting
stays back at the crease and defends to the off side, no seam movement there
shot of the afternoon! Bravo wasn't budging from his crease, stayed where he was and simply punched it through the line off the front foot, the ball whizzed wide of mid-off, that's confidence for you
punched towards mid-on and the fielder had to slide to his left, he deflected the ball towards mid-off but the batsmen decide against the second run
stays back and defends back to the bowler
opens the face of the bat a bit late and dabs it down to third man, well placed
clipped down to midwicket for a single
shuffles and clips him down to the vacant square leg region
nips back in after pitching and he anticipates that early enough by shuffling and whipping it down to deep square leg
stays back at the crease and defends to the off side
tries to slash it away past backward point but he ended up chopping it to the fielder
full and in the length to drive, he pushes it straight to mid-off
stays right back at the crease and defends down the pitch, back of a length delivery
slower ball so he had to slam that to beat the covers, Jadeja does well to run after it and cut it off
quicker delivery, forces him to stay back to defend
angles in towards middle and off, clipped to the on side
stay right back and defends to the off side

spoke too soon about Bravo! Good length on the off stump and Bravo attempts to loft him from the crease and clear mid-on, the bat face turns a bit and he mistimes it, easy catch for Ashwin at mid-on, very soft dismissal
lands it outside off and he shoulders arms

(Hotel) Hyatt checks in and departs immediately! Very similar to Barath's dismissal, Vinay teases him outside the off stump, Hyatt really has to play at it because it was very close to the off stump, pokes at it and gets a thin edge to the keeper
comes across the stumps and defends down the pitch
sprays it down the leg side and departs
gets beside the line and defends to the off side
That was asking to be smashed, full and wide outside off and Simmons gets on his knee and square drives it forcefully wide of the covers
angles it on the pads and he nudges it to fine leg
stays at the crease and defends to the off side
Ramdin can't resist a slash, shortish outside off and he nearly edged that to the keeper
shapes to drive but gets an inside edge onto his pads, the ball rolls away to the off side and they sneak in a single
keeps it on a good length outside off and he leaves it to the keeper
clips it to the on side, gets an inside edge in fact
swings it in and the batsman tries to force it past the infield on the on side
fullish on the pads and he works it straight to mid-on
holds the length back a bit, he shoulders arms outside the off stump
works it towards backward point for a single

and West Indies slide further! Yadav deserves credit again for that wicket, pitches it up and swings it away, forces him to drive but Ramdin gets it to lob off the top half of the bat, easily taken at backward point by Jadeja
that's a gift for Pollard straight up, angling on the pads and moving away, just a feather touch was enough to send it racing to fine leg
clips him down to square leg
swings it on the pads and he works it down towards mid-on
nips back in off the pitch and he clips him down to midwicket
he hits the deck hard this time and the batsman ducks under the bouncer, close to being called a wide as it was shaping down the leg side as well
It's a no-ball because there were only five in the circle during the bowling Powerplay, driven to mid-off, Sehwag realises his mistake, can afford a laugh
teases him outside the off stump, the ball holds its line before reaching the keeper
gets forward and shoulders arms
pushes it towards point and they contemplate a single
tucked to the on side, they take a quick single and Vinay runs across to cut it off, nearly obstructs the non striker
gets right across his stumps and defends down the pitch
hops at the crease and punches it down to cover
very well flicked by Pollard, Aaron slants it on the pads and pitches it up, not much effort on that short as it sailed over midwicket
and nearly has his man there! Pitches up outside off and has Pollard prodding forward to defend, nearly shaved the outside edge
gets across and clips him down towards midwicket
angles it outside off and he gets beside the line and steers it down to third man who's square
nicely driven off the full face of the bat but straight to mid-off
edged but played with soft hands! Drops well short of Sehwag at slip
Simmons has looked good, short of a good length and he punches it through extra cover for three runs, played confidently by Simmons
four more, that's not a drop but Vinay got a hand to it, pitched up on middle and Pollard drove it back powerfully, it didn't stick and raced away for a boundary
back of a length outside off, chopped it towards third man for a single
Simmons charges down the track and he skied that, short, the field was in, and he tried to swat it over the covers, got a top-edge but was lucky it landed safely, he mistimed it
goodish length outside off, shuffles across to turn it past midwicket for a single
short of a good length on the off, slower, dropped it into the off side and ran across safely
gets forward and defends softly, one slip in place
chips down the track but checks is shot
just straightened after pitching, managed to defend it off the full face
gets across his stumps and paddles it down to fine leg
bowls it flatter and quicker, rocks back and whacks it to long-on
tossed up outside off, he gets across and defends to the off side
Ashwin nearly got that to sneak through and hit the off stump, it skidded through and the batsman managed to angle it to third man
gets forward and defends
risks flicking despite the leg slip hovering around, manages to beat the fielder
gets forward and drives to the off side
gets some slow turn, defends close to the pads
chips down the track on seeing the flight but changes his mind and opts to pad it away, may not be  a bad idea to have a bat-pad fielder
turn! And a bit of bounce, dangerously dabbed wide of first slip, runs down to third man and that's a half-century
goes right across and paddles him down to fine leg
drives square on the off side and they run hard
rocks back and cuts but finds point
steers it towards gully and tells Pollard to stay back
goes on the backfoot and knocks it to the off side, thinks of a single
goes back on the crease and punches him to the deep on the off side, they put pressure on Gambhir and take the second
punched to Gambhir again but only a single
sweeps but miscues it, wide of leg slip
wow! There was hardly any pace on that ball and Pollard stayed at the crease and with one swoop managed to clear long-off, power!
and again! Tossed up on middle and leg and Pollard stays put and carts him over wide long-on

Ashwin has his revenge but Pollard isn't happy with the decision! Gets forward to defend, the ball lobbed off the pads and Parthiv ran forward and took the catch, Ravi gave him out immediately, replays weren't conclusive as to whether the ball clipped the glove or not
pushes it to the off side
comes forward and beats him outside the off stump, close!
Impressive turn! Sammy was foxed as it shot away from him
and again! He's getting sharp turn off that rough outside off, nearly took the edge
gets forward and defends
lunges forward and smothers the turn
very generous with the flight, he chips down the track and drives him down to long-off
stays back and clips him down to midwicket
sprays it down the leg side
gets well forward and pushes it towards cover
nice response from Simmons as he chips down the track and takes on Ashwin who's not afraid to toss it up, takes him downtown over long-on
stays back, waits for the turn and punches him down to cover
pushes it towards cover again
that's plumb and everyone knows it, Sammy stays back at the crease but the ball lands on off , holds its line and traps him in front of the stumps as he tries to flick it away
shoulders arms to the keeper
defends and the ball just beats the fielders close to the batsman
defends towards point and sets off
defends really close to the pads and they appeal half heartdly, think he got some bat on it
gets forward and smothers the spin
steers him to the off side
tries to nudge it past Kohli at leg slip
tucks him just wide of midwicket and they set off
hits the base of the pad when the defends but that was hitting outside the line
stays back and clips him wide of midwicket
picks up the length early, gets on his knee and times the slog really well behind square on the on side
tucks it towards midwicket and Jadeja darts across to try and cut it off
defends this back to the bowler
stays back and chops it down towards cover and sets off for a single
not much turn, stays back and defends
defends on the front foot and Ashwin went up in appeal thinking it hit the pad first
chips down the track and Ashwin fires that quick and flat, he improvises well by checking his shot and clipping it to long-on
gets forward and defends
good improvisation again there, stays back, waits for the turn and cuts well wide of third man, he knew where the fielders were
gives himself a lot of room, he fires it on the leg side and he can only turn it to the on side
defended to the on side
tucks him up a bit for room, cuts but chops it to the off side
through the gate! Jadeja fires this flatter, the ball keeps a bit low and Russell tries to whack it over the on side, misses it completely
tossed up on middle and off and defended to the off side
stays back and punches it with the turn to long-on
stays back and punches him down to the covers
shoulders arms to the keeper
that's a very decent sweep, he was on his knee early, fetched that from middle and finds that gap between deep square leg and deep midwicket
gets well forward and defends
hits him on the pad as he defends, close to the stumps
rocks back and chops it to short cover
chops it to the covers again
shapes to sweep but fails to make proper contact
comes forward and defend
defends close to the pad again
power hit from Rampaul! Stays back at the crease and clubs him over long-on
stays back and cuts
stays back and cuts but finds point, there are three fielders in the ring on the off side
he goes inside out this time, comes forward and chips him high down to deep extra cover
gets forward and takes a single to the on side off an inside edge
turns it towards fine leg
gets forward and pushes it towards cover
fires it flat and quick and he punches it to long-off, beats a diving Jadeja
goes back and cuts him down to point
tossed up and defended softly down the pitch
stays back and cuts him just wide of short third man
gets forward and pushes it to the off side
flatter delivery, rocks back and slaps it to cover
stays back and works it to long-on

Simmons won't carry his bat after all! He sweeps just wide of short fine leg, Jadeja mops up at fine leg and fires the throw to the keeper, Simmons turns around and risks the second run but he's well short
turns back in and he defends
Some uninhibited hitting from Rampaul! Tossed up on middle and leg and slogged high over deep midwicket
sweeps again and he connects well, keeps it along the ground this time, down to long leg
forces it down towards long-on
defends down the track
Rampaul is watchful this time, chooses to defend
Ashwin stops at the crease to tease the batsman, defends again
Six N0.5 off Ashwin! Gets on his knee and goes for the whole hog over deep midwicket
lofts with the turn and just manages to clear cover
atempts to clear wide long-on again but Aaron does really well to dive and stop it in front of the rope
Ashwin's dealing in sixes and Rampaul continues his rampage! Once again targets the deep midwicket boundary
stays at the crease and defends
swings it in and he clips him down to midwicket
Rampaul clears the back leg and gets a top edge that clears the keeper, good work by third man to run across and mop up
makes a bit of room to a length delivery and crashes it to cover
slower ball and that rolled to the keeper! Must have landed on a crack
slower one and shorter, he adjusts well, opens the face and dabs it to third man
he takes on the seamers now, Aaron bowls it short from round the wicket, he swivels and pulls past midwicket, good timing and placement
full toss outside off and he dabs it down to third man, that's his fifty! Well done Ramps!
stays beside the line and taps it to the off side
full delivery swinging in on middle and he works it down to deep midwicket
Roach not doing anything silly here, he gently taps a full delivery down to long-on and gives Rampaul the strike
a textbook drive this time, uses the extra pace, full and outside off, he times this crisply wide of backward point, beats third man
steers it straight to backward point this time
slashes him to the off side again but Jadeja does really well to slide to his right and cut it off, may have saved four there
keeps it straight, defends to the on side
Yadav's not getting in the yorkers, Roach once again comfortably pushes it down the track
he bangs it in short this time and Roach comfortably ducks under it, close to being called a wide
loopy full toss and Rampaul decides not to force it away, happy to defend
reaches out to a full and wide delivery outside off and digs it out to third man
not to be, inside edge this time towards fine leg, Aaron can't seem to find the blockhole
full on the stumps, Rampaul gives himself a hint of room and decides to push it back to the bowler
goes for a swish over the on side but he's beaten for pace, the ball hits his body and rolls away to the off side

that slash over third man which was Jayasuriya's signature shot! Aaron is generous with his width and length, one slam and the ball sailed over third man, for a change Ashwin is not the one leaking a six
nudges it to the on side
fires it on the blockhole outside off, tries to dig it out but misses
bangs it in short and he swings again, swishes at thin air
gives himself room to hammer a full delivery across the line but ends up chopping it down the pitch
slower ball and he gently clips it to the on side to get off the strike
punched off the front foot quite forcefully but finds backward point, deserved a few runs for that shot
and Rampaul goes from strength to strength! Threatening to upstage Simmons here, makes room to a full delivery and carves it over backward point, beats third man
makes room and slams a shorter delivery down to deep cover
Roach gets solidly behind the line and defends, not bad for a No.11
bangs it short and he ducks under the bouncer, no problems
solid in defence again, stays behind the line and defends
where are the yorkers? Don't ask me, no trouble for Roach as he defends another one back down the pitch
quietly pushed back to the bowler
bowls it close to a yorker length, well bowled
full and squeezed towards cover
full and drilled down the ground to long-off
stays back and defends down the track
safely negotiated again, Windies look good to play out 50 overs
full on the stumps and easily pushed towards mid-off
good length on middle and leg and he tucks it to mid-on, field is up
gives him a bit of width and he slams it just wide of cover, well played
responds with a bouncer and Roach just manages to duck under it
short outside off and edged but no slip, third man runs across and mops up
low full toss outside the off stump and pushed towards point
drilled down to long-on
bowls it flatter on the stumps, he can only squeeze it back to the bowler
Dropped great attempt by Vinay! Rampaul falls over as he reaches out and carves it over extra cover, Vinay charges forward and dives, just loses control of the ball
elegant clip off the pads by Roach! Times the clip well and gets good elevation to clear midwicket
clipped over midwicket again and it will just be a single
thick outside edge but third man is very fine, just a single, we're in the 240s now
Rampaul picks the big gap at fine leg, pulls a short delivery behind square and the ball just drops short of the rope
fullish outside off and placed down to cover
makes room and drives a fullish delivery down to long-off
gets beside the line and steers him down to backward point, yells at Rampaul to wait
makes a bit of room and he tries to steer it to the off side but he misses
tucks it to the on side and steals a single
digs it in short and he gently taps it to the off side to bring up the 250! Super going by West Indies, this is the resilience they need to show more often
pulls and gets a top edge but as has been the case tonight with Rampaul it falls short of a fielder, fine leg this time
shapes to pull but plays too early, hits his body and rolls away
like a genuine batsman! Stays back and elegantly punches it off the meat of the bat and beats cover, the fielder gave up the chase
squeezes out a yorker down to long-off
fullish outside the off stump and he fails to make contact
that ball zipped through again! Hit the crack and rolled to the keeper outside off, worrying signs
sprays a yorker length ball down the leg side
well the dinner is getting cold! This time outside off, he sees him chipping down  the track so he sprays it wide, loses control of that
Roach reaches out to a length delivery angling away and lashes it down to third man, vacant spaces there
nudges it off his pads to the on side, Rampaul has a chance to go for another thrash
talk about finishing it with a flourish! Pitched up on middle and leg, Rampaul gives himself room, stays back at the crease and takes Aaron downtown to the right of the sightscreen

inn2.comm: gets behind the line and defends towards point
gets the innings off the mark with a dab towards third man
digs it in a bit short and Sehwag gets on his toes and tucks it towards fine leg
this one just sails over the off stump, brave leave by Gambhir
dabs it down to third man
has a poke at one outside the off stump and nearly feathers it to the keeper
this one slices him in half, completely beats him
first blood to Roach! He lands it on a good length outside off and gets it to shape away, Parthiv pokes at it and the outside edge goes low to Sammy at second slip, just manages to scoop it up
lands it outside off and he shoulders arms
clips him down to midwicket with soft hands and sets off quickly
short of a length on off and middle, forces him on the backfoot to defend
Dropped And Sammy drops a straightforward one! Sehwag helps himself to a drive through the covers but gets a thick edge which flies to Sammy's right and he fluffs it
that raced away like a bullet, seemed like a gently nudge off the hips but he got enough elevation to beat short square leg, great timing too
clips one down to midwicket for a single
slides down the leg side and wide called
Rampaul errs bu giving him width to free his arms, Sehwag rides the bounce and slashes this one several feet over the slips
good length on the line of the off stump, gently pushed to the off side
holds the length back a bit and Sehwag gets beside the line and steers it down to third man
taps it with soft hands towards short cover and tells his partner to wait
Roach makes the same error, too short and wide outside off and Sehwag will slash at those in his sleep, a genuine upper cut this time over the slips
fuller and pushed towards cover
hits the deck hard and the bouncer slants into the right-hander, he ducks under it
amazing stop by Pollard at short cover, Sehwag punched at it
he aims at Gambhir;s head but the batsman does well to hop and fend it off to the on side
punched towards cover and Pollard misfields, ironic because two balls back he affected a brilliant save
punches it towards the off side
short of a length this time and he tucks it down towards mid-on
helmet attack! Sehwag took his eyes off completely off that bouncer and the ball lobs off and lands in the region of fine leg, he's alright, Sehwag's as ice-cool as ever
clips it on the up but safe of Simmons at square leg, gambhir needs to be careful of that fielder
lands it just a shade outside off and he leaves it alone
fends it off with soft hands down to the on side and thinks of a single
uncomfortably tucks a short delivery angling into him, might not be a bad idea to have a short leg in
stays on the back foot and drops it down the pitch
good length just a shade outside off, he drops it down to the off side
just a touch short and angling across him, he gets beside the line and steers him to the off side
slides on the pads and gambhir once again clips it on the up, down to fine leg
classic shot! Fullish and angling across him, he transfers his weight on the front foot, makes sure he makes contact off the middle of the bat and places it in the gap at cover, effortless
angles across him again but he steers it to the off side
taps it with soft hands towards Pollard at point

take that! Gambhir is in disbelief! It was wide and asking to be slashed, he reached out and tried to carve it over the packed infield but little Barath timed his leap very well and plucked it with one hand in the region of short cover
gets on his toes and fends off a rising delivery
turns it towards midwicket
nips back in sharply and traps him high on the pads, Roach gets a bit excited
stays back and drops it down to the off side
tucks it down to midwicket for a quick single
keeps it short and on the body and Kohli does well to hop and defend it
stays beside the line and steers him down to Pollard at backward point
angles it towards the body and he clips it to the on side
nearly gets him first ball, has him driving away from the body and gets an inside edge which trickles past the stumps
fullish in length and he defends
driven firmly through the line and Simmons does well to dive at short cover
angles it outside off and Kohli gets across his stumps and taps it to the off side
punched and in the air, good placement as he picks the gap between cover and mid-off, very safe shot in the end
clipped off the pads and Barath does well at square leg to stop it, the fielding has been agile, save for Sammy's drop
slides down the leg side, wide called
keeps it back of a length and tucks him up for room, he can only tap it down the pitch
the short stuff catches him off guard, Kohli was in two minds whether to hook or leave it, he manages to get a top edge which clears the keeper
clips it towards Simmons at square leg, slight fumble
short and wide and Kohli puts it away, he gets on his toes and slashes it over backward point
big appeal for a caught behind! Kohli pulls and Ramdin and the rest think he either got glove or an edge on it, replays werent conclusive on a deflection, Tony Hill shakes his head
punches it towards third man for a single
steers it towards the off side
tucks him up for room and he defends back to the bowler
full and pushed towards point
and nearly gets an edge! Well bowled Russell, he teases him into the drive and Kohli nearly loses his wicket
shorter and pulled to the deep on the on side, he has protection there
drops it a bit short and he pulls to deep square leg
Dropped Bravo this time! Sammy digs it in short and Sehwag goes for the third man slash, Bravo was behind the ball but a bit late in coming forward, the ball carries on the dive but he fumbles
shaky start for Kohli, lucky rather, gets an inside edge which dribbles past the keeper, fine leg runs across to mop up but dives and fumbles, the culprit - Bravo
chops this one down towards third man
lets it go outside the off stump
clips it away softly towards midwicket
slashes away but safe, Russell was generous with his width and pace, Kohli slashed it hard enough to beat a leaping Pollard at backward point
stays back at the crease and taps it to the off side
Chance? Russell loses his radar and slips it down the leg side, the batsman tries to pull, gets some bat on it according to the umpire, Ramdin fails to hold on
slides this one down the leg side
lets this one go outside the off stump
he has a slash at it outside the off stump, pitched up and close to getting an edge
drives on the up but the ball takes the top half of the bat and sails towards third man, one bounce to the fielder
Sehwag's peppering the third man region! Short and wide and he slashes and the ball races past the vacant slip region
gets beside the line and angles it down to third man
gets forward and drives to the off side
shuffles and clips it close to his pads, Sammy appeals thinking it struck his pads in line with leg stump
gets forward and angles it down to third man
pushes it down to extra cover
full on the pads and easily clipped away down to deep midwicket
the singles seem to be coming easily, gets beside the line and angles it down towards third man
bangs it short outside the off stump, he safely lets it go
fuller and angles it towards the pads, he clips it to the on side
fuller in length and he clips it away more forcefully towards mid-on
angles towards the leg side and rightfully put away, all he has to do is run it down to fine leg, West Indies should be careful not to let things drift
short of a length on  the body and he whips it away to deep square leg
